TM - Focus Punch.name: TM - Focus Punch
TM - Focus Punch.data:
The user focuses its mind before
launching a punch. It will fail if
the user is hit before it is used.

TM - Water Pulse.name: TM - Water Pulse
TM - Water Pulse.data:
The user attacks the target with a
pulsing blast of water. It may also
confuse the target.

TM - Bullet Seed.name: TM - Bullet Seed
TM - Bullet Seed.data:
The user forcefully shoots seeds at
the target. Two to five seeds are
shot in rapid succession.

TM - Giga Drain.name: TM - Giga Drain
TM - Giga Drain.data:
A nutrient-draining attack. The
user's HP is restored by half the
damage taken by the target.

TM - Iron Tail.name: TM - Iron Tail
TM - Iron Tail.data:
The target is slammed with a
steel-hard tail. It may also lower
the target's Defense stat.

TM - Shock Wave.name: TM - Shock Wave
TM - Shock Wave.data:
The user strikes the target with a
quick jolt of electricity. This
attack cannot be evaded.

TM - Secret Power.name: TM - Secret Power
TM - Secret Power.data:
The user attacks the target with a
secret power. Its added effects
vary depending on the user's
environment.

TM - Steel Wing.name: TM - Steel Wing
TM - Steel Wing.data:
The target is hit with wings of
steel. It may also raise the user's
Defense stat.

TM - Skill Swap.name: TM - Skill Swap
TM - Skill Swap.data:
The user employs its psychic power
to exchange Abilities with the
target.

TM - Roost.name: TM - Roost
TM - Roost.data:
The user lands and rests its body.
It restores the user's HP by up to
half of its max HP.

TM - Brine.name: TM - Brine
TM - Brine.data:
If the target's HP is down to about
half, this attack will hit with
double the power.

TM - Endure.name: TM - Endure
TM - Endure.data:
The user endures any attack with at
least 1 HP. Its chance of failing
rises if it is used in succession.

TM - Dragon Pulse.name: TM - Dragon Pulse
TM - Dragon Pulse.data:
The target is attacked with a shock
wave generated by the user's gaping
mouth.

TM - Drain Punch.name: TM - Drain Punch
TM - Drain Punch.data:
An energy-draining punch. The user's
HP is restored by half the damage
taken by the target.

TM - Recycle.name: TM - Recycle
TM - Recycle.data:
The user recycles a held item that
has been used in battle so it can
be used again.

TM - Avalanche.name: TM - Avalanche
TM - Avalanche.data:
An attack move that inflicts double
the damage if the user has been
hurt by the target in the same
turn.

TM - Stealth Rock.name: TM - Stealth Rock
TM - Stealth Rock.data:
The user lays a trap of levitating
stones around the opponent's team.
The trap hurts opponents that
switch into battle.

TM - Captivate.name: TM - Captivate
TM - Captivate.data:
If it is the opposite gender of the
user, the target is charmed into
harshly lowering its Sp. Atk stat.

TM - Dark Pulse.name: TM - Dark Pulse
TM - Dark Pulse.data:
The user releases a horrible aura
imbued with dark thoughts. It may
also make the target flinch.

TM - Sleep Talk.name: TM - Sleep Talk
TM - Sleep Talk.data:
While it is asleep, the user
randomly uses one of the moves it
knows.

TM - Natural Gift.name: TM - Natural Gift
TM - Natural Gift.data:
The user draws power to attack by
using its held Berry. The Berry
determines its type and power.

TM - Leech Life.name: TM - Leech Life
TM - Leech Life.data:
The user drains the target's blood.
The user's HP is restored by half
the damage taken by the target.

TM - Air Slash.name: TM - Air Slash
TM - Air Slash.data:
The user attacks with a blade of air
that slices even the sky. It may
also make the target flinch.

TM - Bug Buzz.name: TM - Bug Buzz
TM - Bug Buzz.data:
The user vibrates its wings to
generate a damaging sound wave. It
may also lower the target's Sp. Def
stat.

TM - Power Gem.name: TM - Power Gem
TM - Power Gem.data:
The user attacks with a ray of light
that sparkles as if it were made of
gemstones.

TM - Razor Wind.name: TM - Razor Wind
TM - Razor Wind.data:
A two-turn attack. Blades of wind
hit opposing Pokémon on the second
turn. Critical hits land more
easily.

TM - Brave Bird.name: TM - Brave Bird
TM - Brave Bird.data:
The user tucks in its wings and
charges from a low altitude. The
user also takes serious damage.

TM - Whirlwind.name: TM - Whirlwind
TM - Whirlwind.data:
The target is blown away, to be
replaced by another Pokémon in its
party. In the wild, the battle
ends.

TM - Nasty Plot.name: TM - Nasty Plot
TM - Nasty Plot.data:
The user stimulates its brain by
thinking bad thoughts. It sharply
raises the user's Sp. Atk.

TM - Thunder Fang.name: TM - Thunder Fang
TM - Thunder Fang.data:
The user bites with electrified
fangs. It may also make the target
flinch or leave it with paralysis.

TM - Ice Fang.name: TM - Ice Fang
TM - Ice Fang.data:
The user bites with cold-infused
fangs. It may also make the target
flinch or leave it frozen.

TM - Fire Fang.name: TM - Fire Fang
TM - Fire Fang.data:
The user bites with flame-cloaked
fangs. It may also make the target
flinch or leave it burned.

TM - Psycho Cut.name: TM - Psycho Cut
TM - Psycho Cut.data:
The user tears at the target with
blades formed by psychic power.
Critical hits land more easily.

TM - Horn Drill.name: TM - Horn Drill
TM - Horn Drill.data:
The user stabs the target with a
horn that rotates like a drill. If
it hits, the target faints
instantly.

TM - Take Down.name: TM - Take Down
TM - Take Down.data:
A reckless, full-body charge attack
for slamming into the target. It
also damages the user a little.

TM - Power Whip.name: TM - Power Whip
TM - Power Whip.data:
The user violently whirls its vines
or tentacles to harshly lash the
target.

TM - Pin Missile.name: TM - Pin Missile
TM - Pin Missile.data:
Sharp spikes are shot at the target
in rapid succession. They hit two
to five times in a row.

TM - Cross Poison.name: TM - Cross Poison
TM - Cross Poison.data:
A slashing attack with a poisonous
blade that may also leave the
target poisoned. Critical hits land
more easily.

TM - Hydro Pump.name: TM - Hydro Pump
TM - Hydro Pump.data:
The target is blasted by a huge
volume of water launched under
great pressure.

TM - Heavy Slam.name: TM - Heavy Slam
TM - Heavy Slam.data:
The user slams into the target with
its heavy body. The more the user
outweighs the target, the greater
its damage.

TM - Electro Ball.name: TM - Electro Ball
TM - Electro Ball.data:
The user hurls an electric orb at
the target. The faster the user is
than the target, the greater the
damage.

TM - Agility.name: TM - Agility
TM - Agility.data:
The user relaxes and lightens its
body to move faster. It sharply
boosts the Speed stat.

TM - Teleport.name: TM - Teleport
TM - Teleport.data:
When used by a Trainer, it switches
the user out no matter what. Wild
Pokémon may flee instantly. When
used out of battle, it will warp
you to the last Pokémon Center.

TM - Stored Power.name: TM - Stored Power
TM - Stored Power.data:
The user attacks the target with
stored power. The more the user's
stats are raised, the greater the
damage.

TM - Hex.name: TM - Hex
TM - Hex.data:
This relentless attack does massive
damage to a target affected by
status problems.

TM - Focus Energy.name: TM - Focus Energy
TM - Focus Energy.data:
The user takes a deep breath and
focuses so that critical hits land
more easily.

TM - Bide.name: TM - Bide
TM - Bide.data:
The user endures attacks for two
turns, then strikes back to cause
double the damage taken.

TM - Heat Crash.name: TM - Heat Crash
TM - Heat Crash.data:
The user slams its target with its
flame- covered body. The more the
user outweighs the target, the
greater the damage.

TM - Tail Slap.name: TM - Tail Slap
TM - Tail Slap.data:
The user attacks by striking the
target with its hard tail. It hits
the target two to five times in a
row.

TM - Hurricane.name: TM - Hurricane
TM - Hurricane.data:
The user attacks by wrapping its
opponent in a fierce wind that
flies up into the sky. It may also
confuse the target.

TM - Psywave.name: TM - Psywave
TM - Psywave.data:
The target is attacked with an odd
psychic wave. The attack varies in
intensity.

TM - Tri Attack.name: TM - Tri Attack
TM - Tri Attack.data:
The user strikes with a simultaneous
three-beam attack. May also burn,
freeze, or leave the target with
paralysis.

Ultra Ball.name: Ultra Ball
Ultra Ball.data:
An ultra-performance Ball that
provides a higher Pokémon catch rate
than a Great Ball.

Great Ball.name: Great Ball
Great Ball.data:
A good, high-performance Ball that
provides a higher Pokémon catch rate
than a standard Poké Ball.

Poké Ball.name: Poké Ball
Poké Ball.data:
A device for catching wild Pokémon.
It is thrown like a ball at the
target.
It is designed as a capsule system.

Net Ball.name: Net Ball
Net Ball.data:
A somewhat different Poké Ball which
works especially well on Water and
Bug-type Pokémon. It's not affected
by moves which change a Pokémon's
typing.

Repeat Ball.name: Repeat Ball
Repeat Ball.data:
A Poké Ball which grows in strength
every consecutive capture of a
species of Pokémon. It powers up even
when using a different type of Poké
Ball. Its power is reset to 1.0x if
you capture something else, or if you
don't capture anything for a few
days.

Timer Ball.name: Timer Ball
Timer Ball.data:
A somewhat different Ball that
becomes progressively better the
more turns there are in a battle.

Luxury Ball.name: Luxury Ball
Luxury Ball.data:
A luxurious Poké Ball which helps grow
your friendship with a Pokémon
quickly. It works well on Pokémon
which evolve due to happiness.

Premier Ball.name: Premier Ball
Premier Ball.data:
A somewhat rare Poké Ball that has
been specially made to commemorate
an event of some sort.

Dusk Ball.name: Dusk Ball
Dusk Ball.data:
A somewhat different Poké Ball that
makes it easier to catch wild Pokémon
at night or in dark places like
caves.

Heal Ball.name: Heal Ball
Heal Ball.data:
A Poké Ball which restores a Pokémon's
HP and eliminates any status
ailment.

Quick Ball.name: Quick Ball
Quick Ball.data:
A somewhat different Poké Ball that
provides a better catch rate if it is
used at the start of a wild
encounter.

Cherish Ball.name: Cherish Ball
Cherish Ball.data:
A quite rare Poké Ball that has been
specially crafted to commemorate
an occasion of some sort.

Antidote.name: Antidote
Antidote.data:
A spray-type medicine.
It lifts the effect of poison from
one
Pokémon.

Burn Heal.name: Burn Heal
Burn Heal.data:
A spray-type medicine.
It heals a single Pokémon that is
suffering from a burn.

Ice Heal.name: Ice Heal
Ice Heal.data:
A spray-type medicine.
It defrosts a Pokémon that has been
frozen solid.

Parlyz Heal.name: Parlyz Heal
Parlyz Heal.data:
A spray-type medicine.
It eliminates paralysis from a single
Pokémon.

Full Restore.name: Full Restore
Full Restore.data:
A medicine that fully restores the HP
and heals any status problems of a
single Pokémon.

Max Potion.name: Max Potion
Max Potion.data:
A spray-type medicine for wounds.
It completely restores the HP of a
single Pokémon.

Hyper Potion.name: Hyper Potion
Hyper Potion.data:
A spray-type medicine for wounds.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon by
120 points.

Super Potion.name: Super Potion
Super Potion.data:
A spray-type medicine for wounds.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon by
60 points.

Full Heal.name: Full Heal
Full Heal.data:
A spray-type medicine.
It heals all the status problems of a
single Pokémon.

Revive.name: Revive
Revive.data:
A medicine that revives a fainted
Pokémon. It restores half the
Pokémon's maximum HP.

Max Revive.name: Max Revive
Max Revive.data:
A medicine that revives a fainted
Pokémon. It fully restores the
Pokémon's HP.

Soda Pop.name: Soda Pop
Soda Pop.data:
A fizzy soda drink.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon by
50 points.

Moomoo Milk.name: Moomoo Milk
Moomoo Milk.data:
Milk with a very high nutrition
content.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon by
100 points.

EnergyPowder.name: EnergyPowder
EnergyPowder.data:
A very bitter medicine powder.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon by
50 points.

Energy Root.name: Energy Root
Energy Root.data:
A very bitter root.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon by
200 points.

Heal Powder.name: Heal Powder
Heal Powder.data:
A very bitter medicine powder.
It heals all the status problems of a
single Pokémon.

Revival Herb.name: Revival Herb
Revival Herb.data:
A very bitter herb.

It revives a Pokémon to half its max
HP if they were fainted.

Ether.name: Ether
Ether.data:
It restores the PP of a Pokémon's
selected move by a maximum of
15 points.

Max Ether.name: Max Ether
Max Ether.data:
It fully restores the PP of a single
selected move that has been learned
by the target Pokémon.

Elixir.name: Elixir
Elixir.data:
It restores the PP of all the
moves learned by the targeted Pokémon
by 10 points each.

Lava Cookie.name: Lava Cookie
Lava Cookie.data:
Lavaridge Town's local specialty.
It heals all the status problems of
one Pokémon.

Berry Juice.name: Berry Juice
Berry Juice.data:
A 20% pure juice made of Berries.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon by
just 20 points.

HP Up.name: HP Up
HP Up.data:
A nutritious drink for Pokémon.
It raises the base HP of a single
Pokémon.

Protein.name: Protein
Protein.data:
A nutritious drink for Pokémon.
It raises the base Attack stat of a
single Pokémon.

Iron.name: Iron
Iron.data:
A nutritious drink for Pokémon.

battle, 6.25% of the holder's HP is
restored at the end of each turn.

When held by a Non-Poison-type
Pokémon, it inflicts 12.5% of damage
at the end of each turn. Pokémon with
the ability Magic Guard are immune to
this effect.

Icy Rock.name: Icy Rock
Icy Rock.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It extends the duration of Snowy
weather to 8 turns, when created by
the item holder.

Smooth Rock.name: Smooth Rock
Smooth Rock.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It extends the duration of Sandstorm
weather to 8 turns, when created by
the item holder.

Heat Rock.name: Heat Rock
Heat Rock.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It extends the duration of Harsh
Sunlight weather to 8 turns, when
created by the item holder.

Damp Rock.name: Damp Rock
Damp Rock.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It extends the duration of Rain
weather to 8 turns, when created by
the item holder.

Grip Claw.name: Grip Claw
Grip Claw.data:
When held by a Pokémon, it causes
binding moves used by the holder to
always continue for 7 turns.

Choice Scarf.name: Choice Scarf
Choice Scarf.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
Holding this item will increase Speed
by 50% when in battle, but only
allows the use of the first move
selected.

Sticky Barb.name: Sticky Barb
Sticky Barb.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It inflicts the holder with 12.5% of
its maximum HP each turn.

If the holder is hit with a move that
makes contact, the Sticky Barb will
latch onto the opponent.

Pokémon with the ability Magic Guard
do not take damage from this item.

Power Bracer.name: Power Bracer
Power Bracer.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will guarantee the
child inherits this Pokémon's Attack
IV.

This item is consumed upon use.

Power Belt.name: Power Belt
Power Belt.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will guarantee the
child inherits this Pokémon's Defense
IV.

This item is consumed upon use.

Power Lens.name: Power Lens
Power Lens.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will guarantee the
child inherits this Pokémon's Sp.Atk
IV.

This item is consumed upon use.

Power Band.name: Power Band
Power Band.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will guarantee the
child inherits this Pokémon's Sp.Def
IV.

This item is consumed upon use.

Power Anklet.name: Power Anklet
Power Anklet.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will guarantee the
child inherits this Pokémon's Speed
IV.

This item is consumed upon use.

Power Weight.name: Power Weight
Power Weight.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will guarantee the
child inherits this Pokémon's HP IV.

This item is consumed upon use.

Shed Shell.name: Shed Shell
Shed Shell.data:
A tough, discarded carapace to be
held
by a Pokémon. It enables the holder
to
switch with a waiting Pokémon in
battle.

Big Root.name: Big Root
Big Root.data:
A Pokémon held item that boosts the
power of HP-stealing moves to let the
holder recover more HP.

Choice Specs.name: Choice Specs
Choice Specs.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
Holding this item will increase Sp.Atk
by 50% when in battle, but only
allows the use of the first move
selected.

Flame Plate.name: Flame Plate
Flame Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Fire-type moves.

Splash Plate.name: Splash Plate
Splash Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Water-type moves.

Zap Plate.name: Zap Plate
Zap Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Electric-type moves.

Meadow Plate.name: Meadow Plate
Meadow Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Grass-type moves.

Icicle Plate.name: Icicle Plate
Icicle Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Ice-type moves.

Fist Plate.name: Fist Plate
Fist Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Fighting-type moves.

Toxic Plate.name: Toxic Plate
Toxic Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Poison-type moves.

Earth Plate.name: Earth Plate
Earth Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Ground-type moves.

Sky Plate.name: Sky Plate
Sky Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Flying-type moves.

Mind Plate.name: Mind Plate
Mind Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Psychic-type moves.

Insect Plate.name: Insect Plate
Insect Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Bug-type moves.

Stone Plate.name: Stone Plate
Stone Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Rock-type moves.

Spooky Plate.name: Spooky Plate
Spooky Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Ghost-type moves.

Draco Plate.name: Draco Plate
Draco Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Dragon-type moves.

Dread Plate.name: Dread Plate
Dread Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Dark-type moves.

Iron Plate.name: Iron Plate
Iron Plate.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Steel-type moves.

Odd Incense.name: Odd Incense
Odd Incense.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It increases the power of Psychic-type
moves by 20%.

If held by a Mr. Mime while breeding,
it may help them produce a Mime Jr.
egg.

Rose Incense.name: Rose Incense
Rose Incense.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It increases the power of Grass-type
moves by 20%.

If held by a Roselia or Roserade while
breeding, it may help them produce a
Budew egg.

Pure Incense.name: Pure Incense
Pure Incense.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It slightly reduces the chance of
encountering wild Pokémon.

If held by a Chimecho while breeding,
it may help them produce a Chingling
egg.

Protector.name: Protector
Protector.data:
A protective item of some sort.
It is extremely stiff and heavy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

Electirizer.name: Electirizer
Electirizer.data:
A box packed with a tremendous
amount of electric energy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

Magmarizer.name: Magmarizer
Magmarizer.data:
A box packed with a tremendous
amount of magma energy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

Dubious Disc.name: Dubious Disc
Dubious Disc.data:
A transparent device overflowing with
dubious data.
Its producer is unknown.

Reaper Cloth.name: Reaper Cloth
Reaper Cloth.data:
A cloth imbued with horrifyingly
strong
spiritual energy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

Razor Claw.name: Razor Claw
Razor Claw.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a sharply hooked claw that ups
the holder's critical-hit ratio.

Razor Fang.name: Razor Fang
Razor Fang.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It may make foes and allies flinch
when the holder inflicts damage.

TM - Hone Claws.name: TM - Hone Claws
TM - Hone Claws.data:
The user sharpens its claws to boost
its Attack stat and accuracy.

TM - Dragon Claw.name: TM - Dragon Claw
TM - Dragon Claw.data:
The user slashes the target with
huge, sharp claws.

TM - Psyshock.name: TM - Psyshock
TM - Psyshock.data:
The user materializes an odd psychic
wave to attack the target. This
attack does physical damage.

TM - Calm Mind.name: TM - Calm Mind
TM - Calm Mind.data:
The user quietly focuses its mind
and calms its spirit to raise its
Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

TM - Roar.name: TM - Roar
TM - Roar.data:
The target is scared off and
replaced by another Pokémon in its
party. In the wild, the battle
ends.

TM - Toxic.name: TM - Toxic
TM - Toxic.data:
A move that leaves the target badly
poisoned. Its poison damage worsens
every turn.

TM - Snowscape.name: TM - Snowscape
TM - Snowscape.data:
A snowstorm forms on the field for 5
turns. Snow boosts the Defense stat
of Ice-types by 50%.

TM - Bulk Up.name: TM - Bulk Up
TM - Bulk Up.data:
The user tenses its muscles to bulk
up its body, boosting both its
Attack and Defense stats.

TM - Venoshock.name: TM - Venoshock
TM - Venoshock.data:
The user drenches the target in a
special poisonous liquid. Its power
is doubled if the target is
poisoned.

TM - Hidden Power.name: TM - Hidden Power
TM - Hidden Power.data:
An attack which varies in type
depending on its user. Its type may
be changed with 40 Gems.

TM - Sunny Day.name: TM - Sunny Day
TM - Sunny Day.data:
The user intensifies the sun for
five turns, powering up Fire-type
moves.

TM - Taunt.name: TM - Taunt
TM - Taunt.data:
The target is taunted into a rage
that allows it to use only attack
moves for three turns.

TM - Ice Beam.name: TM - Ice Beam
TM - Ice Beam.data:
The target is struck with an
icy-cold beam of energy. It may
also freeze the target solid.

TM - Blizzard.name: TM - Blizzard
TM - Blizzard.data:
A howling blizzard is summoned to
strike the opposing team. It may
also freeze them solid.

TM - Hyper Beam.name: TM - Hyper Beam
TM - Hyper Beam.data:
The target is attacked with a
powerful beam. The user must rest
on the next turn to regain its
energy.

TM - Light Screen.name: TM - Light Screen
TM - Light Screen.data:
A wondrous wall of light is put up
to suppress damage from special
attacks for five turns.

TM - Protect.name: TM - Protect
TM - Protect.data:
It enables the user to evade all
attacks. Its chance of failing
rises if it is used in succession.

TM - Rain Dance.name: TM - Rain Dance
TM - Rain Dance.data:
The user summons a heavy rain that
falls for five turns, powering up
Water-type moves.

TM - Telekinesis.name: TM - Telekinesis
TM - Telekinesis.data:
The user makes the target float with
its psychic power. The target is
easier to hit for three turns.

TM - Safeguard.name: TM - Safeguard
TM - Safeguard.data:
The user creates a protective field
that prevents status problems for
five turns.

TM - Frustration.name: TM - Frustration
TM - Frustration.data:
A full-power attack that grows more
powerful the less the user likes
its Trainer.

TM - SolarBeam.name: TM - SolarBeam
TM - SolarBeam.data:
A two-turn attack. The user gathers
light, then blasts a bundled beam
on the second turn.

TM - Smack Down.name: TM - Smack Down
TM - Smack Down.data:
The user throws a stone or
projectile to attack an opponent. A
flying Pokémon will fall to the
ground when hit.

TM - Thunderbolt.name: TM - Thunderbolt
TM - Thunderbolt.data:
A strong electric blast is loosed at
the target. It may also leave the
target with paralysis.

TM - Thunder.name: TM - Thunder
TM - Thunder.data:
A wicked thunderbolt is dropped on
the target to inflict damage. It
may also leave the target with
paralysis.

TM - Earthquake.name: TM - Earthquake
TM - Earthquake.data:
The user sets off an earthquake that
strikes those around it.

TM - Return.name: TM - Return
TM - Return.data:
A full-power attack that grows more
powerful the more the user likes
its Trainer.

TM - Dig.name: TM - Dig
TM - Dig.data:
The user burrows, then attacks on
the second turn. It can also be
used to exit dungeons.

TM - Psychic.name: TM - Psychic
TM - Psychic.data:
The target is hit by a strong
telekinetic force. It may also
reduce the target's Sp. Def stat.

TM - Shadow Ball.name: TM - Shadow Ball
TM - Shadow Ball.data:
The user hurls a shadowy blob at the
target. It may also lower the
target's Sp. Def stat.

TM - Brick Break.name: TM - Brick Break
TM - Brick Break.data:
The user attacks with a swift chop.
It can also break any barrier such
as Light Screen and Reflect.

TM - Double Team.name: TM - Double Team
TM - Double Team.data:
By moving rapidly, the user makes
illusory copies of itself to raise
its evasiveness.

TM - Reflect.name: TM - Reflect
TM - Reflect.data:
A wondrous wall of light is put up
to suppress damage from physical
attacks for five turns.

TM - Sludge Wave.name: TM - Sludge Wave
TM - Sludge Wave.data:
It swamps the area around the user
with a giant sludge wave. It may
also poison those hit.

TM - Flamethrower.name: TM - Flamethrower
TM - Flamethrower.data:
The target is scorched with an
intense blast of fire. It may also
leave the target with a burn.

TM - Sludge Bomb.name: TM - Sludge Bomb
TM - Sludge Bomb.data:
Unsanitary sludge is hurled at the
target. It may also poison the
target.

TM - Sandstorm.name: TM - Sandstorm
TM - Sandstorm.data:
A five-turn sandstorm is summoned to
hurt all combatants except the
Rock, Ground, and Steel types.

TM - Fire Blast.name: TM - Fire Blast
TM - Fire Blast.data:
The target is attacked with an
intense blast of all-consuming
fire. It may also leave the target
with a burn.

TM - Rock Tomb.name: TM - Rock Tomb
TM - Rock Tomb.data:
Boulders are hurled at the target.
It also lowers the target's Speed
by preventing its movement.

TM - Aerial Ace.name: TM - Aerial Ace
TM - Aerial Ace.data:
The user confounds the target with
speed, then slashes. The attack
lands without fail.

TM - Torment.name: TM - Torment
TM - Torment.data:
The user torments and enrages the
target, making it incapable of
using the same move twice in a
row.

TM - Facade.name: TM - Facade
TM - Facade.data:
An attack move that doubles its
power if the user is poisoned,
burned, or has paralysis.

TM - Flame Charge.name: TM - Flame Charge
TM - Flame Charge.data:
The user cloaks itself with flame
and attacks. Building up more
power, it raises the user's Speed
stat.

TM - Rest.name: TM - Rest
TM - Rest.data:
The user goes to sleep for two
turns. It fully restores the user's
HP and heals any status problem.

TM - Attract.name: TM - Attract
TM - Attract.data:
If it is the opposite gender of the
user, the target becomes infatuated
and less likely to attack.

TM - Thief.name: TM - Thief
TM - Thief.data:
An attack which steals the foe's
held item if the user isn't already
holding one. Its effects are
temporary when stealing from
Trainers.

TM - Low Sweep.name: TM - Low Sweep
TM - Low Sweep.data:
The user attacks the target's legs
swiftly, reducing the target's
Speed stat.

TM - Round.name: TM - Round
TM - Round.data:
The user attacks the target with a
song. Others can join in the Round
and make the attack do greater
damage.

TM - Overheat.name: TM - Overheat
TM - Overheat.data:
The user attacks the target at full
power. The attack's recoil harshly
reduces the user's Sp. Atk stat.

TM - Focus Blast.name: TM - Focus Blast
TM - Focus Blast.data:
The user heightens its mental focus
and unleashes its power. It may
also lower the target's Sp. Def.

TM - Energy Ball.name: TM - Energy Ball
TM - Energy Ball.data:
The user draws power from nature and
fires it at the target. It may also
lower the target's Sp. Def.

TM - False Swipe.name: TM - False Swipe
TM - False Swipe.data:
A restrained attack that prevents
the target from fainting. The
target is left with at least 1 HP.

TM - Scald.name: TM - Scald
TM - Scald.data:
The user shoots boiling hot water at
its target. It may also leave the
target with a burn.

TM - Fling.name: TM - Fling
TM - Fling.data:
The user flings its item at the foe,
destroying it. In PvP, only
consumable items are destroyed
permanently. The move's power and
effects vary depending on what item
is thrown.

TM - Charge Beam.name: TM - Charge Beam
TM - Charge Beam.data:
The user attacks with an electric
charge. The user may use any
remaining electricity to raise its
Sp. Atk stat.

TM - Incinerate.name: TM - Incinerate
TM - Incinerate.data:
The user attacks the target with
fire. If the target is holding a
Berry, the Berry becomes burnt up
and unusable.

TM - Will-O-Wisp.name: TM - Will-O-Wisp
TM - Will-O-Wisp.data:
The user shoots a sinister,
bluish-white flame at the target to
inflict a burn.

TM - Acrobatics.name: TM - Acrobatics
TM - Acrobatics.data:
The user nimbly strikes the target.
If the user is not holding an item,
this attack inflicts massive
damage.

TM - Explosion.name: TM - Explosion
TM - Explosion.data:
The user explodes to inflict damage
on those around it. The user faints
upon using this move.

TM - Shadow Claw.name: TM - Shadow Claw
TM - Shadow Claw.data:
The user slashes with a sharp claw
made from shadows. Critical hits
land more easily.

TM - Payback.name: TM - Payback
TM - Payback.data:
If the user moves after the target,
this attack's power will be
doubled.

TM - Retaliate.name: TM - Retaliate
TM - Retaliate.data:
The user gets revenge for a fainted
ally. If an ally fainted in the
previous turn, this attack's damage
increases.

TM - Giga Impact.name: TM - Giga Impact
TM - Giga Impact.data:
The user charges at the target using
every bit of its power. The user
must rest on the next turn.

TM - Rock Polish.name: TM - Rock Polish
TM - Rock Polish.data:
The user polishes its body to reduce
drag. It can sharply raise the
Speed stat.

TM - Stone Edge.name: TM - Stone Edge
TM - Stone Edge.data:
The user stabs the foe with
sharpened stones from below. It has
a high critical-hit ratio.

TM - Volt Switch.name: TM - Volt Switch
TM - Volt Switch.data:
After making its attack, the user
rushes back to switch places with a
party Pokémon in waiting.

TM - Thunder Wave.name: TM - Thunder Wave
TM - Thunder Wave.data:
A weak electric charge is launched
at the target. It causes paralysis
if it hits.

TM - Gyro Ball.name: TM - Gyro Ball
TM - Gyro Ball.data:
The user tackles the target with a
high-speed spin. The slower the
user, the greater the damage.

TM - Swords Dance.name: TM - Swords Dance
TM - Swords Dance.data:
A frenetic dance to uplift the
fighting spirit. It sharply raises
the user's Attack stat.

TM - Struggle Bug.name: TM - Struggle Bug
TM - Struggle Bug.data:
While resisting, the user attacks
the opposing Pokémon. The targets'
Sp. Atk stat is reduced.

TM - Psych Up.name: TM - Psych Up
TM - Psych Up.data:
The user hypnotizes itself into
copying any stat change made by the
target.

TM - Bulldoze.name: TM - Bulldoze
TM - Bulldoze.data:
The user stomps down on the ground
and attacks everything in the area.
Hit Pokémon's Speed stat is
reduced.

TM - Frost Breath.name: TM - Frost Breath
TM - Frost Breath.data:
The user blows a cold breath on the
target. This attack always results
in a critical hit.

TM - Rock Slide.name: TM - Rock Slide
TM - Rock Slide.data:
Large boulders are hurled at the
opposing team to inflict damage. It
may also make the targets flinch.

TM - X-Scissor.name: TM - X-Scissor
TM - X-Scissor.data:
The user slashes at the target by
crossing its scythes or claws as if
they were a pair of scissors.

TM - Dragon Tail.name: TM - Dragon Tail
TM - Dragon Tail.data:
The user knocks away the target and
drags out another Pokémon in its
party. In the wild, the battle
ends.

TM - Poison Jab.name: TM - Poison Jab
TM - Poison Jab.data:
The target is stabbed with a
tentacle or arm steeped in poison.
It may also poison the target.

TM - Dream Eater.name: TM - Dream Eater
TM - Dream Eater.data:
The user eats the dreams of a
sleeping target. It absorbs half
the damage caused to heal the
user's HP.

TM - Grass Knot.name: TM - Grass Knot
TM - Grass Knot.data:
The user snares the target with
grass and trips it. The heavier the
target, the greater the damage.

TM - Swagger.name: TM - Swagger
TM - Swagger.data:
The user enrages and confuses the
target. However, it also sharply
raises the target's Attack stat.

TM - Pluck.name: TM - Pluck
TM - Pluck.data:
The user pecks the target. If the
target is holding a Berry, the user
eats it and gains its effect.

TM - U-turn.name: TM - U-turn
TM - U-turn.data:
After making its attack, the user
rushes back to switch places with a
party Pokémon in waiting.

TM - Substitute.name: TM - Substitute
TM - Substitute.data:
The user makes a copy of itself
using some of its HP. The copy
serves as the user's decoy.

TM - Flash Cannon.name: TM - Flash Cannon
TM - Flash Cannon.data:
The user gathers all its light
energy and releases it at once. It
may also lower the target's Sp. Def
stat.

TM - Trick Room.name: TM - Trick Room
TM - Trick Room.data:
The user creates a bizarre area in
which slower Pokémon get to move
first for five turns.

Magma Stone.name: Magma Stone
Magma Stone.data:
A scorching hot stone which may be
used to alter the IVs of certain
Pokémon by 1.

Consumed upon use.

Red Apricorn.name: Red Apricorn
Red Apricorn.data:
A red Apricorn.
It assails your nostrils.

Blu Apricorn.name: Blu Apricorn
Blu Apricorn.data:
A blue Apricorn.
It smells a bit like grass.

Ylw Apricorn.name: Ylw Apricorn
Ylw Apricorn.data:
A yellow Apricorn.
It has an invigorating scent.

Grn Apricorn.name: Grn Apricorn
Grn Apricorn.data:
A green Apricorn.
It has a mysterious, aromatic scent.

Pnk Apricorn.name: Pnk Apricorn
Pnk Apricorn.data:
A pink Apricorn.
It has a nice, sweet scent.

Wht Apricorn.name: Wht Apricorn
Wht Apricorn.data:
A white Apricorn.
It doesn't smell like anything.

Blk Apricorn.name: Blk Apricorn
Blk Apricorn.data:
A black Apricorn
It has an indescribable scent.

Fast Ball.name: Fast Ball
Fast Ball.data:
A Poké Ball which is excellent at
capturing Pokémon with high base
Speed.

Level Ball.name: Level Ball
Level Ball.data:
A Poké Ball which is excellent at
capturing Pokémon who are the same
level as yours.

Lure Ball.name: Lure Ball
Lure Ball.data:
A Poké Ball for catching Pokémon
hooked
by a Rod when fishing.

Heavy Ball.name: Heavy Ball
Heavy Ball.data:
A Poké Ball for catching very heavy
Pokémon.

Love Ball.name: Love Ball
Love Ball.data:
A Poké Ball which is excellent at
capturing Pokémon of the same
evolution line as yours, but of the
opposite gender. It doesn't help
against genderless foes.

Friend Ball.name: Friend Ball
Friend Ball.data:
A Poké Ball which makes a Pokémon very
happy upon capture. It works well on
Pokémon which evolve due to
happiness.

Moon Ball.name: Moon Ball
Moon Ball.data:
A Poké Ball for catching Pokémon that
evolve using the Moon Stone.

RageCandyBar.name: RageCandyBar
RageCandyBar.data:
A famous Mahogany Town candy tourists
like to buy and take home. It
restores
the HP of one Pokémon by 20 points.

Prism Scale.name: Prism Scale
Prism Scale.data:
A mysterious scale that evolves
certain Pokémon.
It shines in rainbow colors.

Eviolite.name: Eviolite
Eviolite.data:
A mysterious evolutionary lump. When
held, it raises the Defense and Sp.
Def
of a Pokémon that can still evolve.

Float Stone.name: Float Stone
Float Stone.data:
A very light stone. It reduces the
weight of a Pokémon when held.

Rocky Helmet.name: Rocky Helmet
Rocky Helmet.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
If the holder of this item is hit by a
move that makes contact, it will
inflict damage on the attacker for
16.67% of their maximum HP per-hit.

Air Balloon.name: Air Balloon
Air Balloon.data:
When held by a Pokémon, the Pokémon
will float into the air. When the
holder
is attacked, this item will burst.

Ring Target.name: Ring Target
Ring Target.data:
Moves that would otherwise have no
effect will land on the Pokémon that
holds it.

Binding Band.name: Binding Band
Binding Band.data:
When held by a Pokémon, it causes the
damage inflicted by binding moves
used by the holder to increase from
12.5% to 16.7% of the opponent's
maximum HP at the end of each turn.

Absorb Bulb.name: Absorb Bulb
Absorb Bulb.data:
A consumable bulb. If the holder is
hit
by a Water-type move, its Sp. Atk
will rise.

Cell Battery.name: Cell Battery
Cell Battery.data:
A consumable battery. If the
holder is hit by an Electric-type
move, its Attack will rise.

Eject Button.name: Eject Button
Eject Button.data:
If the holder is hit by an attack, it
will
switch with another Pokémon in
your party.

Fire Gem.name: Fire Gem
Fire Gem.data:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It increases the power of Fire-type
moves by 50%.

This item is consumed upon use.

Water Gem.name: Water Gem
Water Gem.data:

Pretty Wing.data:
Though this feather is beautiful,
it's
just a regular feather and has no
effect on Pokémon.

Dream Ball.name: Dream Ball
Dream Ball.data:
A Poké Ball which becomes more
effective the longer a wild Pokémon
is asleep.

BalmMushroom.name: BalmMushroom
BalmMushroom.data:
A rare mushroom which gives off a
nice
fragrance.
A maniac will buy it for a high
price.

Big Nugget.name: Big Nugget
Big Nugget.data:
A big nugget of pure gold that gives
off
a lustrous gleam.
A maniac will buy it for a high
price.

Pearl String.name: Pearl String
Pearl String.data:
Very large pearls that sparkle in a
pretty silver color.
A maniac will buy them for a high
price.

Comet Shard.name: Comet Shard
Comet Shard.data:
A shard which fell to the ground when
a comet approached.
A maniac will buy it for a high
price.

Casteliacone.name: Casteliacone
Casteliacone.data:
Castelia City's specialty, soft-serve
ice cream. It heals all the status
problems of a single Pokémon.

TM - Wild Charge.name: TM - Wild Charge
TM - Wild Charge.data:
The user shrouds itself in
electricity and smashes into its
target. It also damages the user a
little.

TM - Snarl.name: TM - Snarl
TM - Snarl.data:
The user yells as if it is ranting
about something, making the
target's Sp. Atk stat decrease.

Cover Fossil.name: Cover Fossil
Cover Fossil.data:
A fossil of an ancient Pokémon that
lived in the sea in ancient times.
It appears to be part of its back.

Plume Fossil.name: Plume Fossil
Plume Fossil.data:
A fossil of an ancient Pokémon that
flew in the sky in ancient times.
It appears to be part of its wing.
